Frontend Requirements (Structured)

1) Feature: Create a New Bill
  - User Story: As an administrator/tester, I want to register a new service bill so I can track and later pay it.
  - UI/Pages:
    • "New Bill" screen/form
  - Data Model (bill):
    • clientId (string/int)
    • serviceType (enum: Water, Electricity, Sewer)
    • billingPeriod (string, format YYYYMM)
    • amount (number, USD)
    • status (Pending | Paid)
  - Inputs:
    • Client ID (selectable dropdown or free text input)
    • Service Type (dropdown)
    • Billing Period (text input capped to YYYYMM)
    • Amount (numeric input)
  - Validation Rules:
    • All fields are required.
    • Billing period must match regex ^\d{6}$ (YYYYMM).
    • Amount must be > 0.
    • Client must exist (validate against client list/API).
  - Acceptance Criteria:
    • Submitting a valid form sends a request to create a bill (POST /bills).
    • The created bill is persisted with status "Pending".
    • UI provides clear success notification.
    • Validation errors are shown for missing/invalid inputs.

2) Feature: Pay an Existing Bill
  - User Story: As a user, I want to pay an existing unpaid bill so my balance is updated.
  - UI/Pages:
    • "Pay Bill" screen/form
  - Inputs:
    • Client ID
    • Service Type
    • Billing Period (YYYYMM)
  - Validation Rules:
    • All fields are required.
    • Client must exist.
    • Billing period must be a valid YYYYMM.
    • There must be an existing unpaid bill for the provided criteria.
  - Acceptance Criteria:
    • Submitting a valid payment sends a request to pay (POST /payments).
    • The corresponding bill status updates to "Paid".
    • UI displays a confirmation on success.
    • Errors are shown when bill is missing or already paid.

3) Feature: View Pending Bills
  - User Story: As a user, I want to see all outstanding bills for a client.
  - UI/Pages:
    • "Pending Bills" list view / table
  - Inputs:
    • Client ID (lookup)
  - Display Columns:
    • Service Type
    • Billing Period
    • Amount
    • Current Status
  - Behavior:
    • Lists only unpaid bills (status == Pending) for the selected client.
    • Data fetched via GET /clients/{id}/pending-bills (OData-supported filtering).
  - Optional Enhancements:
    • Inline action to pay a bill directly from the list.

4) Feature: View Payment History
  - User Story: As a user, I want to review previously paid bills.
  - UI/Pages:
    • "Payment History" list view / table
  - Inputs:
    • Client ID
  - Display Columns:
    • Service Type
    • Billing Period
    • Amount Paid
    • Payment Date
    • Status
  - Behavior:
    • Lists paid bills for the selected client, ordered chronologically.
    • Data fetched via GET /clients/{id}/payment-history (OData-supported filtering).
  - Optional Enhancements:
    • Filtering/sorting by service, date, or amount.

5) General Technical Requirements (applies to all features)
  - Technology:
    • React (TypeScript) OR Angular (TypeScript) OR Flutter (Dart).
  - Architecture:
    • Use a modern component-based architecture.
    • Use a global state management solution:
      - React: Redux Toolkit (preferred) or Context + useReducer (with justification).
      - Angular: NgRx.
      - Flutter: Bloc, Riverpod, or Provider.
  - API Integration:
    • Use OData for querying/filtering endpoints.
    • Include JWT Authorization headers on all API requests.
  - UI:
    • Use a modern UI framework:
      - Web: TailwindCSS, Bootstrap, Material UI, etc.
      - Flutter: Material Design 3 / native widget system.
    • Build responsive UI (desktop + mobile).
  - Quality:
    • Write code in a typed language (TypeScript or Dart).
    • Avoid deprecated libraries (e.g., jQuery).
    • Include unit and/or automated tests for key logic (components/hooks/views/services).
    • Strong typing and robust error handling.
    • Modular, maintainable, scalable code structure.

6) API Contract (aligned to backend requirements)
  - Create bill: POST /bills
    • Payload: { clientId, serviceType, billingPeriod, amount }
    • Response: bill object including status.
  - Pay bill: POST /payments
    • Payload: { clientId, serviceType, billingPeriod }
    • Response: updated bill object or payment receipt.
  - Pending bills: GET /clients/{id}/pending-bills
    • Supports OData query params for filtering/sorting.
  - Payment history: GET /clients/{id}/payment-history
    • Supports OData query params for filtering/sorting.

7) Evaluation & Delivery
  - Evaluation criteria:
    • Implementation quality, best practices, completeness, organization, readability, maintainability.
  - Delivery expectations:
    • Use a GitHub repository.
    • Include a README explaining:
      - API functionality.
      - How to build and run the application.
      - Any features or requirements not implemented, with reasons.
